-- Russia Supports Kim as Next World Bank President, Siluanov Says
-- B y   S c o t t   R o s e
-- 2012-04-13T16:55:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-13/russia-supports-kim-as-next-world-bank-president-siluanov-says.html
Russia will vote in favor of
Dartmouth College President Jim Yong Kim, the U.S. nominee to
head the  World Bank , Finance Minister Anton Siluanov said.  “Kim is a world-class professional who has experience in
practical work,” Siluanov said today in an e-mailed statement
after meeting Kim in Moscow. “The BRICS countries set
professional qualities at the top of their list when discussing
candidates to be president of the World Bank.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Scott Rose in Moscow at 
 rrose10@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  